      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Shared Script</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marc Desmond letter on Democratic convention's parading liberals and Republicans hiding conservatives; says both parties feign concern for constituencies they otherwise ignore (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You say (news article, Aug. 16) that the Democratic National Convention's ''cavalcade of liberals was in decided contrast to the Republican convention, when conservative figures, the most steadfast party loyalists, were largely kept offstage.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You say (news article, Aug. 16) that the Democratic National Convention's ''cavalcade of liberals was in decided contrast to the Republican convention, when conservative figures, the most steadfast party loyalists, were largely kept offstage.''</p>
        <p>But the two parties did exactly the same thing: they used their conventions to feign concern for constituencies whose beliefs and interests they have otherwise ignored.</p>
        <p>MARC DESMOND  Brooklyn, Aug. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
